@group orders
@endpoint POST /orders
@desc Create an order in the eCommerce system.With the exception of the 'id' field, the required fields indicated in the 'Order' model are those required to create a new order.The paymentStatus can only be AWAITING_PAYMENT or INCOMPLETE.The fulfillmentStatus can only be AWAITING_PROCESSING
@required {order: map # The order object to be created}
@returns(200) OK - Everything worked as expected
@errors {400: Bad Request - Often due to a missing request parameter, 401: Unauthorized - An invalid element token, user secret and/or org secret provided, 500: Server error - Something went wrong on the Cloud Elements server, 403: Forbidden - Access to the resource by the provider is forbidden, 502: Provider server error - Something went wrong on the Provider or Endpoint's server, 404: Not found - The requested resource is not found, 415: Unsupported media type - The server cannot handle the requested Content-Type, 405: Method not allowed - Incorrect HTTP verb used, e.g., GET used when POST expected, 406: Not acceptable - The response content type does not match the 'Accept' header value, 409: Conflict - If a resource being created already exists}

@endpoint GET /orders
