@endpoint PATCH /orders/{id}
@desc Update an order associated with a given ID in the eCommerce system. The update API uses the PATCH HTTP verb, so only those fields provided in the order object will be updated, and those fields not provided will be left alone. Updating an order with a specified ID that does not exist will result in an error response</strong>
@required {id: any # The ID of the order to update in the eCommerce system, order: map # The order object, with those fields that are to be updated}
@optional {action: any # An action to perform on the order: cancel, reopen or close. If left blank then the order is updated but no action is taken}
